summary: the critics from fan-content sites love detective pikachu tho. which means that not only is the execution good, but they know...
question: the critics from fan-content sites love detective pikachu tho. which means that not only is the execution good, but they know that the ppl who made the movie really made sure its for everyone to enjoy
answer:
Yeah, I trust that more.

Like here’s the thing. The ‘real’ critics praised Endgame but from what I heard, it’s not that good and it doesn’t deserve the 98% on Rotten Tomatoes. Like they’re trying to put this on the same level as Black Panther because of the hype. Really? Yet they’re judging Detective Pikachu differently. These are both nerdy properties and both from huge franchises so why not treat them the same?

I mean people don’t have to love the movie but I find it just a tad unfair.

summary: What’s really going to impress me about Detective Pikachu, is that they are going all out. They’re not just sticking to the...
body: What’s really going to impress me about Detective Pikachu, is that they are going all out. They’re not just sticking to the Kanto or first few generations. They are using each and every generation of Pokémon, so every fan of every age can recognize their favorites. They may not animate all 809 species, but they’re doing a real good job putting in as many as they can. THAT is dedication to detail
